  1→//! Disk cache for [`BehaviorMap`]s and [`FunctionSpec`]s, enabling persistence across runs.
  2→//!
  3→//! When shatter explores a function, the resulting behavior map is stored to disk
  4→//! so it can be reloaded in future runs — critical for compositional testing where
  5→//! function B's behavior map is reused when testing function A.
  6→//!
  7→//! Cache entries include the protocol version so that protocol upgrades
  8→//! automatically invalidate stale entries.
  9→
 10→use std::fs;
 11→use std::path::{Path, PathBuf};
 12→
 13→use serde::{Deserialize, Serialize};
 14→
 15→use crate::behavior::BehaviorMap;
 16→use crate::protocol::PROTOCOL_VERSION;
 17→use crate::spec::FunctionSpec;
